This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method based on importance sampling to handle a larger vocabulary. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with improving the performance of machine translation models. The paper also mentions the use of LSTM-based neural machine translation models, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of BLEU as a metric for translation performance, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as BLEU is commonly used in image captioning tasks.
